#Approach:

Leaders in an Array – Approach

Leader wo element hota hai jo apne right side ke sab elements se bada ho.
Rightmost element hamesha leader hota hai.

Isliye array ko right se traverse karte hain aur ek variable maxi rakhte hain
jo ab tak ka right side ka maximum element store karta hai.

Agar current element maxi se bada ho, to wo leader hai,
usse list me add karo aur maxi update kar do.

Kyuki hum right se leaders add kar rahe hain,
isliye end me list ko reverse kar dete hain taki order same rahe.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public List<Integer> leaders(int[] nums) {

        List<Integer> aList = new ArrayList<>();
        int n = nums.length;
        int maxi = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            if(nums[i] > maxi){
                aList.add(nums[i]);
                maxi = nums[i];
            }
        }
        Collections.reverse(aList);
        return aList;
    }
}
